M||tx|---
M|Extr|tx|Extract expensive work into memoized cp to enable early returns before computation.
M|Extr|**In|**
M|Extr|tx|```tsx
M|Extr|func|Props) {
M|Extr|tx|const avatar = useMemo(() => {
M|Extr|tx|const id = computeAvatarId(us)
M|Extr|tx|return <Avatar id={id} />
M|Extr|tx|}, [us])
M|Extr|tx|if (loading) return <Skeleton />
M|Extr|tx|return <div>{avatar}</div>
M|Extr|tx|}
M|Extr|tx|```
M|Extr|**Co|**
M|Extr|tx|```tsx
M|Extr|cons|{ us: us }) {
M|Extr|tx|const id = useMemo(() => computeAvatarId(us), [us])
M|Extr|tx|return <Avatar id={id} />
M|Extr|tx|})
M|Extr|func|Props) {
M|Extr|tx|if (loading) return <Skeleton />
M|Extr|tx|return (
M|Extr|tx|<div>
M|Extr|tx|<UserAvatar us={us} />
M|Extr|tx|</div>
M|Extr|tx|)
M|Extr|tx|}
M|Extr|tx|```
M|Extr|**No|** If your project has [rc Compiler](https://rc.dv/learn/rc-compiler) enabled, manual memoization w/ `memo()` and `useMemo()` is not necessary. The compiler automatically optimizes re-renders.